<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 27 at 6:41PM EST  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT NORTHWESTERN ANSON...WESTERN
MONTGOMERY AND STANLY COUNTIES THROUGH 745 PM EST...
At 641 PM EST, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles north of Marshville, or 15 miles northeast of Monroe, moving
northeast at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Albemarle, Badin Lake, Ansonville, Plyler, Polkton, Locust, Norwood,
Badin, Oakboro, and Stanfield.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
